<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 11:25PM CDT  by NWS Lake Charles</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Hardin
County through MIDNIGHT CDT...
At 1125 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sour Lake, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Beaumont, Lumberton, Silsbee, Kountze, Sour Lake and Bevil Oaks.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
southeastern Texas.</instruction>
